OL,3,GGrampian
OL,4,
OL,5,CToday:FSome brightness in the west to
OL,6,Fstart but cloudy in the east, heavy
OL,7,Fand possibly thundery showers
OL,8,Fdeveloping at times, a few brighter
OL,9,Fspells too. Light winds.
OL,10,
OL,11,CTonight:FShowers slowly dying out but
OL,12,Fquite a cloudy evening in places with
OL,13,Fsome mist and fog possible. Winds
OL,14,Fstrengthening overnight and feeling
OL,15,Fquite muggy and warm.
OL,16,
OL,17,CSaturday:FA bright and mostly dry
OL,18,Fstart to the weekend but warm and
OL,19,Fwindy, some showers developing for
OL,20,Fupper Deeside in the afternoon and
OL,21,Fpossibly drifting east.
OL,23,QppppppppppppppppppppGSource: Met Office
OL,24,ANext Page  BWeather  CReg News  FReg TV
